comments.body: per @mzelesky We are seeing barcodes in the processed CSV files in lib-sftp that do not exist in Alma -> if the file is refilled in SCSB then it is not in Alma anymore. This job is one day behind so this is always a possibility.

> Barcode: `33433016615068` : We checked in alma and has no `due date` even though the due date exists in the file. It appears in two files: scsb_renewal_export_202205190612.csv.processed and scsb_renewal_export_202205200612.csv.processed

We checked in ALma and the Process type for this barcode is 'In transit'. This is why there is no due date.

This error was fixed by https://github.com/pulibrary/lib_jobs/pull/330/files
closing and opening a new issue after discussing with @mzelesky https://github.com/pulibrary/lib_jobs/issues/335

comments.body: In this specific case, I'm referring to when the email failed to send in the end. Basically, if the job fails to run to completion for any reason, we need to be alerted.

Checking for email being sent itself is question beyond just this job. Given the our current mail relay structure the machine that actually sends the email out to the wide world is not the application server running the job: https://github.com/pulibrary/lib_jobs/issues/320.
Ah, so the job on lib-jobs has no way of knowing if the email went out.
